= Vote of No Confidence

[? if in_grand_coalition : The PSL ?][? if in_weimar_coalition or in_popular_front or in_minority_government: The Center Party ?] has called for a vote of no confidence against us, due to our various policies and disagreements. If this succeeds, there will be an election in a few months.

@vonc_menu

- @try_assuage: Try to assuage our partners.
- @support_lewica: Could we get the Lewica to abstain?
- @let_it_happen: Let the vote happen.

@try_assuage

How do we assuage our partners?

- @give_up_prussia: Give up on leadership of Prussia.
- @austerity: Enact a massive austerity plan.
- @resources: Use our resources to reduce dissent within the coalition.
- @support_lewica: Could we get the Lewica to abstain?
- @let_it_happen: Never mind. Let the vote happen.

@give_up_prussia
view-if: razem_prussia == 1
on-arrival: coalition_dissent = 0; razem_prussia = 0; prussian_government = "I"; reformist_dissent += 10; centrist_dissent += 10; labor_dissent += 10; left_dissent += 5; workers_razem -= 5; rural_razem -= 5; 

Fine. We no longer control the government of Prussia. The vote has been called off.

@austerity
view-if: welfare >= 0 and not secularized
on-arrival: coalition_dissent = 0; workers_razem -= 10; unemployed_razem -= 10; workers_lewica += 7; workers_korona += 3; unemployed_lewica += 5; unemployed_korona += 5; left_dissent += 15; center_dissent += 10; labor_dissent += 15; reformist_dissent += 5; welfare -= 2; budget += 1; unemployed += 3; lewica_coalition_dissent += 1; lewica_relation -= 10 if in_popular_front

Fine. We enacted a massive austerity program to cut welfare, in order to maintain the stability of our coalition. The vote has been called off.

@resources
view-if: secularized = 0
choose-if: resources >= 3
unavailable-subtitle: We do not have enough resources.
subtitle: -3 resources
on-arrival: resources -= 3; coalition_dissent -= 1;

By transferring resources to our coalition partners, we can reduce their dissent against our policies. This is a crude, but effective solution.

@support_lewica
choose-if: (in_grand_coalition and communist_coalition >= 3 and lewica_relation >= 50 and lewica_r >= psl_r) or (in_weimar_coalition and lewica_relation >= 50 and lewica_r >= z_r and communist_coalition >= 3)
view-if: tried_supporting_lewica = 0
on-arrival: tried_supporting_lewica = 1
unavailable-subtitle: [? if communist_coalition < 3 : The Lewica won't take part in parliamentary government. ?] [? if lewica_relation < 50 : The Lewica is not friendly enough with us. ?] [? if (in_grand_coalition and lewica_r < psl_r) or (in_weimar_coalition and lewica_r < z_r): The Lewica does not have enough votes. ?] [? if in_popular_front : We are already in a Popular Front with the Lewica. ?]

If the Communists abstain, then we essentially can maintain a minority government[? if president=="Hindenburg":, although it would be very difficult to make policy without the support of President Hindenburg, which we do not have ?]. If this happens, then we will own a massive debt to the Lewica. This could lead to broader cooperation in the future, for better or for worse.

- @support_lewica_2: Persuade the Lewica to "tolerate" us?
- @let_it_happen: Never mind. Let the vote happen.

@support_lewica_2
on-arrival: communist_coalition += 1; workers_lewica += 3; lewica_relation += 5
go-to: support_lewica_weimar if in_weimar_coalition; support_lewica_grand if in_grand_coalition

